South Africa has recorded 548 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 545 979. The country has also recorded 47 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Monday. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the North West. “Regrettably, we report 47 more COVID-19 related deaths: 3 from Eastern Cape, 2 from the Free State, 15 from Gauteng, 0 from Kwa-Zulu Natal, 0 from Limpopo, 0 from Mpumalanga, 23 from the North West, 1 from the Northern Cape and 3 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize.  This brings the total number of deaths to 52 710. Recoveries currently stand at 1 472 645. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 9 819 994. The number of healthcare workers vaccinated under the Sisonke Protocol stands at 239 665. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 545 979 the total number of deaths is 52 710 the total number of recoveries is 1 472 645 and the total number of vaccines administered is 239 665. pic.twitter.com/UPlLhaUWEf — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) March 29, 2021 